firmest feeling mattress and the Purple 4 is the softest.","<strong>Purple 2: My Sleep Experience</strong>","The online mattress company sent the Purple 2 to our lab. Oddly, this one didn’t come in a purple bag – like the original did. It was already fully expanded, but inside of a box, which made it a pain to get to my apartment. Purple mattresses are far heavier than most mattresses we reviewed, so moving it from work to my apartment was not fun.","From speaking with a representative from Purple, we learned the company temporarily stopped bagging its mattresses, which is when we ordered ours. Now the Purple 2 and 3 come compressed and rolled into a bag while the Purple 4 is too heavy to roll and compress, so it comes full size.","The cover on this mattress looks great. It has a white top with gray sidewalls, and the top has the Purple logo woven into the fabric. The design looks exceptionally clean – better than the original. It’s almost a shame to cover it with a fitted mattress sheet.","The Purple 2 is the model most like the original in terms of feel, though the 2 felt a bit firmer to me. In fact, it took me longer to get used to the Purple 2 than the original.","I’m not used to sleeping on a firm mattress. While I’m not saying it was like sleeping on a board by any means, it’s firmer than my current mattress and I did wake up with some back soreness after the first few nights I slept on it – something I didn’t experience with the original Purple.","Although it feels too firm for me, I can’t deny how supportive the mattress is. I generally sleep on my back or stomach, but mostly my stomach. I could feel the mattress pushing up against my lower back when I was resting on my back, but it also cradled my upper back – keeping my spine aligned. I’ve maintained this sentiment – the Purple mattress doesn’t feel like any other mattress I’ve ever slept on – and that’s a good thing. Ultimately, after about four days, I got used to the mattress and really enjoyed sleeping on it. The break-in period was longer, and since this mattress is $600 more expensive than the original Purple queen-sized mattress – I’d still buy the original over this one. If you want a softer feel, the Purple 3 and 4 both provide a plusher feeling, but at $1899 and $2499, both are significantly more expensive than all other mattresses we reviewed.","Finally, the mattress sleeps cool. The hyper-polymer grid, combined with the mattress cover, allows for plenty of breathability. Never during my trial did I feel too hot during sleep.","<strong>Purple 2: Delivery and Returns</strong>","Purple makes its mattresses on an order-by-order basis. Depending on the current order list, it could take up to a few weeks for your mattress to be shipped to your home.","Purple offers 100-day trials on its mattresses. Although we have not returned this mattress, when we returned the original <a href=\"/purple-review\">Purple </a>mattress, the customer service staff was nice and helpful. You have to verify the return via email and pick how you choose to return the mattress: return to a charity, manually take it to a recycler or let the company choose a charity. After the mattress was returned, we received a full refund with no hassle."]},"id":"0ec455fd-ef67-410c-8aa8-fb8a38f8a479","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"5e8d2e43-4b54-4efc-a091-8a506c94f5d7","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["This mattress was firmer than I expected but still provided amazing support after I got used it. The new models, including the Purple 2 that I received for testing, are more expensive than products from other online mattress companies. I still think the original Purple mattress is the better buy compared to the Purple 2 – it’s truer to a medium feel and will save you $600. However, I still think Purple is probably the best online mattress product out there."]},"id":"73dd13ca-92b1-4710-8b3b-c83aad3724d4","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_69951","url":"/p